				<td colspan="2"><span>The tasks seem to follow a kind of sick logic.  the &quot;short&quot; tasks are just a quick jaunt around Kunark something like go somewhere close, then head to a zone 1 screen away, then go to one 2 screens away from your origonal spot and hail some random guy who should know better than to stand next to the wurm spawn point without invis.
<br />

<br />
The Medium tasks will also try to send you to another zone in kunark but this time you're looking at keyed zones.
<br />

<br />
Seblis
<br />
The howling stones
<br />
Veshaans peak
<br />

<br />
Not sure what else but I'm guessing that the tasks were set up with 2 things in mind.
<br />

<br />
most people will start the game these days with at least the everquest trilogy meaning that they will have access to antonica, faydwer, odus, kunark, possibly velious and the Plane of Knowledge.  And where do we find our taskmasters?  Kunark, Faydwer, antonica and POK.
<br />

<br />
I'm wondering what taskmasters in the Plane of Nightmares might do considering that the only tasks I've gotten so far require you to know how to solo effectivly (not hard for a bard but for a cleric or a warrior in his late 60s?  Not easy in any shape.
<br />

<br />
Now from what i've heard a medium task at 65 will net you 20% aa exp.  if you can solo effectively or get a group that's some good change for so little work.  
<br />

<br />
The only other option I can see at this point is to box yourself a group which is &quot;Forbidden&quot; so I can't see sony making a feature that requires this kind of logic.
<br />

<br />
Send them feedback it's the only way they'll learn.</span></td>
